        "tab_wJQBqL": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "jewellery care",
            "content": "<h3>ðŸ’Ž <strong>Jewellery Care Guide</strong></h3><p>At <strong>Sparkle Jewels</strong>, each piece is crafted with precision to be cherished for a lifetime. Proper care ensures your <strong>natural or lab-grown diamond jewellery</strong> keeps its brilliance and beauty for years.</p><h4><strong>1. Everyday Habits & What to Avoid</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Last On, First Off</strong> Wear jewellery <em>after</em> makeup, perfume, hairspray, or lotion. Remove it <em>before</em> bathing or sleeping.</li><li><strong>Avoid Harsh Chemicals & Chlorine</strong> Remove jewellery before swimming or cleaning. Chlorine, bleach, and cleaning agents can weaken gold and damage rhodium plating (in white gold).</li><li><strong>Remove During Physical Activities</strong> Take off jewellery before gym workouts, household chores, gardening, or heavy lifting to avoid bending or loosening settings.</li><li><strong>Handle with Care</strong> Gold is soft, especially <strong>22K & 18K</strong>. Avoid bumps or stacking heavy pieces to prevent scratches and dents.</li></ul><h4><strong>2. Cleaning & Maintenance</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Gentle Cleaning at Home</strong> Soak jewellery in lukewarm water with mild soap. Brush gently with a soft toothbrush, rinse, and pat dry with a microfiber or lint-free cloth.</li><li><strong>Wipe After Every Wear</strong> Oils and sweat can dull diamonds. A quick wipe with a soft cloth maintains sparkle.</li><li><strong>Avoid Abrasive Cleaners</strong> <em>Never</em> use toothpaste, harsh chemicals, or rough clothsâ€”they can scratch gold and loosen prongs.</li><li><strong>Professional Polishing & Rhodium Replating</strong> White gold may need rhodium replating over time. Yellow & rose gold benefit from occasional polishing.</li></ul><h4><strong>3. Storage Tips</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Store Separately</strong> Keep pieces in soft pouches or lined jewellery boxes to avoid scratches.</li><li><strong>Keep Dry & Cool</strong> Avoid humid places like bathrooms; moisture can tarnish gold and affect diamond shine.</li><li><strong>Travel Carefully</strong> Use individual pouches or soft-lined travel cases to prevent scratches or bending.</li></ul><h4><strong>4. Diamond & Setting Care</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Natural & Lab-Grown Diamonds</strong> Both require the same careâ€”regular cleaning restores sparkle.</li><li><strong>Check Settings Regularly</strong> Have prongs or clasps inspected once or twice a year by a professional to prevent stone loss.</li><li><strong>Avoid Ultrasonic Cleaners at Home</strong> Fragile designs may not withstand ultrasonic vibrations. Leave deep cleaning to professionals.</li></ul><h4><strong>5. Quick Care Checklist</strong></h4><p>âœ… Remove before swimming, exercising, or cleaning</p><p>âœ… Clean gently with mild soap & lukewarm water</p><p>âœ… Wipe after each wear with a soft cloth</p><p>âœ… Store pieces separately in a dry, cool place</p><p>âœ… Get professional inspection & polishing once a year</p><p>âœ¨ Following these simple steps will keep your <strong>gold & diamond jewellery</strong> (natural or lab-grown) shining beautifully for years to come.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_wCf6Gt": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Return & Exchange Policy",
            "content": "<h3>ðŸ’Ž <strong>Sparkle Jewels Return & Exchange Policy</strong></h3><p>Welcome to the <strong>Sparkle Returns Program</strong>!</p><p>We want you to love your jewellery. If not completely satisfied, our <strong>15-day, no-questions-asked return & exchange policy</strong> makes returns simple and fair.</p><h4><strong>1. Return & Exchange Window</strong></h4><ul><li>Available within <strong>15 days</strong> from the date of delivery.</li><li>Jewellery must be unworn, in original packaging, and accompanied by the original certificate & invoice.</li></ul><h4><strong>2. Defective / Damaged Items</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>100% refund or exchange</strong> if the item is damaged or incorrect, upon inspection post-return.</li></ul><h4><strong>3. Regular Returns (No Defect)</strong></h4><ul><li>Returns are subject to a <strong>â‚¹1500 shipping/handling fee</strong> deducted from the refund.</li><li>Exchanges receive <strong>100% value</strong> applied to a new purchase.</li></ul><h4><strong>4. High-Value Transactions</strong></h4><ul><li>Orders above <strong>â‚¹100,000</strong> are eligible for <strong>exchange only</strong>â€”no direct refund.</li></ul><h4><strong>5. Non-Returnable Items</strong></h4><ul><li>Customized or engraved pieces.</li><li>Loose solitaires (covered under a separate buyback policy).</li><li>International orders are not covered under this policy.</li></ul><h4><strong>6. How to Initiate a Return/Exchange</strong></h4><ol><li><strong>Email support@sparklejewels.in</strong> (cc: your order number) within 15 days of delivery.</li><li>Provide your order number, invoice, certificate copy, and photos of the piece.</li><li>Once approved, we'll send return instructions and a pre-paid shipping label (where available).</li><li>Return the item to undergo quality inspection and valuation.</li><li>Upon approval, refunds or exchange credits are processed within <strong>10-14 business days</strong> via your original payment mode (minus â‚¹1500 if applicable).</li></ol><h4><strong>7. Policy Constraints</strong></h4><ul><li>Only <strong>one return/exchange per invoice</strong> under this 15-day plan.</li><li>If you've already completed an exchange via this policy, further returns are not eligible.</li><li>The value of any freebies/gifts returned will be deducted proportionally.</li><li>Refunds will exclude any discount portions from promotions.</li></ul><h4><strong>8. After 15 Days</strong></h4><ul><li>All requests after 15 days are ineligible under this policy. Only our standard <strong>Buyback & Exchange Policy</strong> applies.</li></ul><h4><strong>9. Shipping & Liability</strong></h4><ul><li>A prepaid label will be used where available; otherwise, you pay for return shipping.</li><li>We are not liable for returned packages that do not show valid tracking.</li></ul><h4><strong>10. Processing Timeline</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Inspection & valuation:</strong> Up to 5 business days after receipt.</li><li><strong>Refund/replacement:</strong> 15-20 business days after customer approval.</li></ul><h4><strong>Reach Out Anytime</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Email:</strong> sparklejewels1386@gmail.com</li><li><strong>Phone/WhatsApp:</strong> +91-8980462440</li></ul>"
          }
        }
